Themes & Shades

Composer (Templates)

  • Theme: site.custom – Shade: null
  • Theme: site.custom-solar – Shade: null

Bootswatch

  • Theme: site.light – Shade: light
  • Theme: site.dark – Shade: dark
  • Theme: site.solar-light – Shade: dark (same as site.solar-dark)
  • Theme: site.solar-dark – Shade: dark
  • Theme: site.css_alt – Shade: dark
  • Theme: site.css_alt – Shade: null

Water.css

  • Theme: html.light – Shade: light
  • Theme: html.dark – Shade: dark
  • Theme: html.css_alt – Shade: dark
    • (automatic prefers-color-scheme color selection)
  • Theme: html.css_alt – Shade: null (default: html)
    • (automatic prefers-color-scheme color selection)
  • Theme: html.solar-light – Shade: dark
  • Theme: html.solar-dark – Shade: dark
  • Theme: html.solar-css_alt – Shade: dark (default: site)
    • (automatic prefers-color-scheme color selection)
  • Theme: html.solar-css_alt – Shade: null
    • (automatic prefers-color-scheme color selection)

Markdown Viewer

  • Theme: html.alt-light – Shade: light
  • Theme: html.alt-dark – Shade: dark
  • Theme: html.alt-solar-light – Shade: dark
  • Theme: html.alt-solar-dark – Shade: dark
  • Theme: html.alt-css_alt – Shade: dark

Reveal.js

  • Theme: revealjs.light – Shade: null
  • Theme: revealjs.dark – Shade: null (default: revealjs)
  • Theme: revealjs.solar-light – Shade: null
  • Theme: revealjs.solar-dark – Shade: null
  • Theme: revealjs.css_alt – Shade: null

<!-- composer >> {composer_root}/index.md.cms -->

Composer README
Created with c_site, and configured to produce a navigable reference document.
Introduction
Main page, with information about this test site and how to use it.
Default Site
An empty configuration, to demonstrate a simple page with no layout or elements.
Configured Site
All settings changed, showcasing the full flexibility of layout and behavior.
Pandoc Markdown
A Pandoc markdown file, without any Composer embedded elements.
Bootstrap Default
A markdown file with default Bootstrap colors instead of themes and shades.
Layout & Elements
All documentation for c_site layout and embeddable page elements, with examples.
Metainfo Page
A longer page assembled from a collection of files and their metadata, with instructions.
Metainfo File
A single file from the collection above, showing how to span metadata across contexts.
Themes & Shades
Gallery of included themes and shades, for all HTML-based formats.
Default Library Page
Starting page for the library, which is a digest of the most recently dated files.
Configured Library Page
Same as above, for a version of the library specific to the config directory.
